'''[[time]] [[trial]]'''

# (cycling) An unpaced race in which riders (or teams), leaving at regular intervals (e.g., every 30 sec, or every minute), are timed over a pre-set course/distance with the winner being the rider (or team) to finish in the fastest time. Known colloquially as the ''race of truth''. There are two variations: ITT (individual time trial) and TTT (team time trial).
# any [[competitive]] [[event]] in which [[competitor]]s are [[timed]] rather than [[racing]] against each other

